# ============================================================================
# _thrum — zsh completion for thrum, a JZZ-backed livecoding MIDI sequencer
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/ryanramage/thrum
#   Author     : Ryan Ramage
#   License    : ISC
#   Stars      : 14
#   Language   : JavaScript (Node.js)
#   npm        : thrum v5.0.0
#   Binary     : thrum  (package.json bin → ./livecoding.js)
#   Last push  : 2025-12-24
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   thrum is "a livecoding music sequencer using functional reducers" — Ryan
#   Ramage's Node.js CLI for music livecoding.  The user authors a `song`
#   module (e.g. `song.js`) that exports an object with a `.tick(state)`
#   reducer function;  thrum loads the module, opens a MIDI output via
#   JZZ, and runs the tick function on every beat / bar, sending the
#   resulting NoteOn / NoteOff / Controller events to the MIDI device.
#   The `fs.watch`-based file watcher reloads the song module on every
#   save (with `require.cache` invalidated for files under the project
#   root, skipping `node_modules`), so the musician can hot-reload
#   melody / harmony / arrangement code while the sequencer keeps
#   running.  Music-theory helpers come from `@tonaljs/tonal`.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from livecoding.js — rc-based config +
#                       a single positional)
#   thrum [--key VALUE]... [--config FILE] <song.js>
#
#   Positional argument:
#     <song.js>          Music file exporting a `song` object with a
#                        `.tick()` method (required; without it, the CLI
#                        prints usage + available MIDI ports and exits)
#
#   rc-style config (rc('thrum', defaults)).  Any of these can be set via:
#     - `--key value` on the command line
#     - `THRUM_<KEY>` environment variables
#     - JSON in `.thrumrc` files (cwd / $HOME / /etc/)
#     Keys consumed by livecoding.js:
#       --port <N>             listening port for the editor bridge
#                                                          [default: 5551]
#       --in <NAME>            MIDI input device name (autopicks first
#                              available if unset)
#       --out <NAME>            MIDI output device name (autopicks first
#                              available if unset)
#       --config <FILE>        rc's standard --config <FILE> override
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `jzz ^1.0.2` declared in package.json — the
#   canonical Node.js MIDI library by jazz-soft (588 stars, JZZ on npm).
#   JZZ wraps Jazz-Plugin / native MIDI on Linux (ALSA), macOS (CoreMIDI),
#   Windows (WinMM) and the Web MIDI API in browsers behind a single
#   chainable API.  thrum loads it as `const JZZ = require('jzz')` then
#   uses `JZZ().info().inputs / .outputs` to enumerate ports and
#   `midiOut.send([0x90 + channel, note, velocity])` to emit NoteOn /
#   NoteOff / Controller messages each beat.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/ryanramage/thrum/contents/package.json
#       → "jzz": "^1.0.2"
#     gh api repos/ryanramage/thrum/contents/livecoding.js
#       → const JZZ = require('jzz')
#       → JZZ().or('Cannot start MIDI engine!')
#   This entry is the TS-Node=118 leader bump that CLOSES Axis 63
#   (MIDI I/O Library) at 1/1/1 three-language symmetry:
#     Rust   = midir                       (R841, `devalang`, devaloop-labs)
#     Go     = gitlab.com/gomidi/midi/v2   (R842, `melrose`,  emicklei)
#     TS-Node = jzz ^1.0.2                  (R843, `thrum`,    ryanramage)
#   Reaches the triple-118 landmark Rust=Go=TS-Node=118.
#
#   No completion for `thrum` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_thrum() {
    _arguments -s \
        '--port=[editor-bridge port (default 5551)]:port:' \
        '--in=[MIDI input device name (autopick first if unset)]:input device:' \
        '--out=[MIDI output device name (autopick first if unset)]:output device:' \
        '--config=[rc config file override]:config file:_files -g "*.(json|js|rc)"' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show usage and list available MIDI ports]' \
        ':song module:_files -g "*.(js|mjs|cjs)"'
}

_thrum "$@"
